 sarah alma mater dartmouth college harvard university immelt at us climate action partnership event in  immelt left in the polish senate in  jeffrey robert immelt born february   is an american business executive he is currently the chairman of the board of the usbased conglomerate general electric he was selected as ges ceo by their board of directors in  to replace jack welch upon welchs retirement from ge previously immelt had headed up ges medical systems division now known as ge healthcare as its president and ceo effective august   immelt will step down as ges ceo contents  early life  career  general electric  background  crisis management  strategy  divestitures  acquisitions and investments  performance  employment  controversies  compensation and retirement  philanthropy  charitable activities  public service  honors  career honors  commencement addresses  personal life  references  further reading  external links early lifeedit immelt was born in cincinnati the son of donna rosemary née wallace a school teacher and joseph francis immelt who managed the general electric aircraft engines division geae is now known as ge aviation immelt attended finneytown high school he played football in college and was an offensive tackle he earned an ab in applied mathematics and economics cum laude  from dartmouth college graduating with the class of  he was president of his fraternity phi delta alpha and currently serves on the dartmouth board of trustees during his years at dartmouth he worked summers on a ford assembly line in cincinnati after graduating he worked for procter and gamble before matriculating at harvard for his mba immelt earned his mba from harvard business school graduating in  he described business school as one of the most intense times of your life  careeredit general electricedit backgroundedit immelt has been with ge since  when he graduated from harvard with his mba he held a number of increasingly senior positions in ges plastics appliances and healthcare businesses he became a ge officer in  joined the ge capital board in  and took on the leadership of ge healthcare before being named ceo the competition for the ceo position that immelt won began when jack welch asked gary wendt the head of ge financial services inc then a  billion empire and ges most profitable division to resign on the theory that he would overshadow welchs other candidates immelt surpassed robert nardelli who was so close to welch that his nickname was little jack and james mcnerney nardelli would leave ge to head home depot and then chrysler and mcnerney left ge to lead m before going on to lead boeing immelt was selected by the ge board in november  to succeed welch as ceo of ge he served as ges president and chairmanelect for ten months before taking the position of chairman and ceo of ge on september   he will retire from ge on december   crisis managementedit immelt has been thrust into three significant external crises since taking the lead at ge as chairman on september   almost immediately he faced the  terrorist attacks he then was pressed to defend ges business model and the quality of its financial reports as the economy reeled from the enron crisis in  he shepherded ge through the united states financial crisis his tenure as chairman and ceo started off on a low note – he took over the role on september   just four days before the terrorist attacks on the united states which killed two employees and cost ges insurance business  million as well as having a direct effect on the companys aircraft engines sector immelt defended ges reporting elections and the quality of its financial statements following heightened scrutiny after the enron crisis in  his first year end as ceo immelt famously offered the market and the sec a choice in financial reports a new dramatically expanded set of reports with more details versus what had been the traditional format for ges sec filings the experiment seemed to confirm that the traditional format which was shorter was preferable and it continues to be used at ge today immelts intuition and judgments about financial reporting transparency were validated in experiments in behavioral economics conducted at princeton in  immelt has led ge through two reporting challenges since then it has been required to restate its sec filings and in  ge agreed to pay the sec  million to settle allegations of accounting fraud ge could not escape the  crisis that was fueled by the mortgagebacked securities debacle on wall street and the liquidity crisis that brought the derivatives market to its knees ges major financial business is known as ge capital and it is operated largely through the general electric credit corporation subsidiary as part of its response to the credit crisis ge joined goldman sachs and morgan stanley in forming a wholly owned banking affiliate that qualified as a savings and loan association this entitles the subsidiary to fdic insurance over its deposit at the cost of bowing to regulation as a bank holding company aid received from the federal reserve by ge has also become a political issue in the  presidential campaign strategyedit immelt has not been a passive inheritor of the house that jack built  in fact at the outset of this time as ges ceo immelt took pains to establish that he would act as his own man  welch preferred internal or organic growth and benefited from longterm us economic trends that buoyed his major business lines in particular welchs tenure benefited from the economic expansion during the clinton administration which ended immediately before immelt became ges ceo the us economy has faced a number of shocks since immelt became ceo the  terrorist attacks on the usa the  financial crisis and the recessionary quarters under the obama administration immelts governance has taken a different path differentiating him from welch in both substance and style on the one hand he has eliminated or reduced ges involvement in a number of businesses from the welch era with moves in the plastics appliance and ge capital businesses on the other hand he has seized the growing international nature of commerce to expand ges operations overseas divestituresedit the ge plastics business was sold in  for  billion to saudi arabian interests welch had been the leader of ges plastics business before being named its overall ceo in  ge agreed to sell its appliance business for  billion  in  immelt completed the sale of nbc universal to comcast for  billion in april  ge announced a major series of reorganization steps it plans to sell its real estate business for  billion sell most of its ge capital assets which now total  billion and repatriate nearly  billion in cash held overseas to fund while the board also authorized a share buyback program using up to  billion this plan confirms ges intent to exit the banking business acquisitions and investmentsedit immelts reorganization of ge has been accomplished in part through a number of acquisitions he underscored the riskiness of an acquisitionbased growth strategy in  when he said you cant do a lot of deals and have them all be great  geographically his strategy has focused on two areas china and europe ges efforts in china have been central to immelts vision in july  immelts general electric announced that it is in the process of relocating its xray division from wisconsin to china immelt had previously referred to china as ges second home market immelt initiated one of his first major acquisitions in his area of operating expertise the medical business in  ge bought uk based amerhsam plc for  billion ge is currently attempting to complete its acquisition of alstom france businesses for an enterprise value of  billion  at the same time immelt has taken a number of actions that have been controversial with some leading to bad publicity a major headline grabber has been the reduction in ges workforce at the same time that immelt served on a presidential council whose aim was to increase us employment see public service section performanceedit on march   according to its fiscal  sec form k ge had  shares of voting common stock outstanding with an aggregate market value  billion on march   on january   according to its fiscal  sec form k ge had  shares of voting common stock outstanding with an aggregate market value of at least  billion on the last business day of ges most recently completed second fiscal quarter since taking over ges stock price has dropped  while income has risen from  billion in  to  billion in  at the ten year mark of immelts tenure at ge its stock price had dropped  from its levels when he took over during that same year period ge has paid out  billion in dividends the sp  index has roughly doubled in value since immelt took over employmentedit at the end of  when immelt replaced welch ge employed  worldwide and  in the us as reported in its sec form k for  ges sec form k for  states that worldwide employment is  and us employment is  these employment levels have varied significantly under immelt general electric year end employment has varied from  in  to  in  a net increase of  employment had dropped from  in  to  in  controversiesedit immelt has been associated in the press with a number of public controversies he is working with the nfl to find a constructive medical solution to the headtrauma injury issues faced by football players of all types immelts role concerning employment and unemployment is his greatest controversy he served on a presidential council whose goal included increasing employment in the us while leading ge during more than a decade of volatility in the number of people it employs those believing his business roles contributed to unemployment have demonstrated at his college speeches the number of people employed by ge has been volatile as a performance statistic both rising and falling that volatility reflects both ge cost cutting efforts under ge and the acquisition and sale of several large businesses each with their own significant number of employees immelts strategies have contributed to a buildup of cash at the end of  over  billion had been kept offshore to avoid a special federal repatriation tax as such ge is a member of a controversial group of american companies experiencing trapped cash thought to exceed  trillion across this group of corporations in  ge announced a repatriation program for part of its cash balances after the us fiscal crisis of – immelt reduced ges dividends to conserve capital and internal funding causing a negative reaction among some dividendoriented investors he recently began a public campaign to press the state of connecticut for local tax benefits and threatened to move some of ges operations out of the state if the benefits were not forthcoming as chairman and ceo of ge immelt has come under attack for leading ge towards legally avoiding paying us federal corporate taxes ges tax positions have become a major item in immelts agenda ges local taxes in connecticut have increased  times since  and the state had approved yet another revised tax policy in early  immelt threatened to move ges headquarters out of connecticut if the state would not back away from the tax plan during the us presidential elections in  ge came under attack for not paying us federal taxes while receiving substantial federal tax benefits while the tax attacks created the impression that ge paid no taxes its worldwide tax expense was over  billion with most of the taxes paid in foreign jurisdictions ge is reported to have paid no federal us taxes in  compensation and retirementedit immelts compensation has fluctuated significantly as ceo of general electric in  immelt earned a total compensation of  in  he earned a total compensation of  in  immelt earned a total compensation of  in  immelts compensation nearly doubled to  million immelt had a total five year compensation of  million through  an income which ranked sixth among executives employed by usbased conglomerates some components of his total compensation package over the years have been newsworthy in some years he was granted stock options at  and in other years he was paid no bonusin  his compensation totalled  million a decrease from his  compensation of  million that  compensation had risen  over his  compensation of  million on june   ge announced that is chairman and ceo jeffrey r immelt would retire to be replaced by john l flannery philanthropyedit charitable activitiesedit immelt serves on the board of two nonprofit organizations one of which is the robin hood foundation a charitable organization which attempts to alleviate problems caused by poverty in new york city he has also served on the board of catalyst a not for profit organization dedicated to advancing women in business he was elected a charter trustee of his alma mater dartmouth in  and as of  continues in that role he has also served dartmouth on its alumni council and as a class officer immelt has spoken about the benefits of football to his career from his experiences as a former player as ge ceo he has taken a leadership position in finding solutions to the risk of head trauma injuries among nfl players he announced a series of initiatives with nfl commissioner goodell including a ge investment of  million to develop diagnostic equipment for use in head trauma injuries and ges participation in a separate  million effort to develop safer helmets and other equipment he has personally participated in the als ice bucket challenge in which celebrities are videoed pouring buckets of ice water over themselves and the videos are then posted online to help raise charitable funds for the als association the ge foundation has been extolled as a leader in corporate charitable giving since immelt became ge ceo with special attention to its efforts to support schools in the us over and above its university activities and healthcare in poor countries under immelt ge frequently appears in lists of notably charitable us corporations for example ge was pictured no  in  with charitable disbursements of  million in a ranking published by forbes immelt has returned to his hometown high school finneytown to contribute to the finneytown schools education foundation the foundation established the jeff immelt award for leadership in football public serviceedit immelt served as chairman of the business council a nonpartisan organization in  and  it is notable that two ge ceos reginald jones and jack welch each also served in this capacity immelt was named a member of the board of the federal reserve bank of new york in  he resigned the board position in  as one of americas top ceos immelt has been a leading proponent of diversity in the work place saying if youre serious about  making the world work better the only discriminating factor should be excellence in other words ge is committed to diversity because  its the only way to do business right  ge is committed to employing a diverse workforce with the most innovative minds in the world  in february  in the early days of the obama administration immelt was appointed as a member to the presidents economic recovery advisory board to provide the president and his administration with advice and counsel in fixing americas economic downturn when president obama chose to put jeffrey immelt at the head of the economic advisory board he felt that immelt had attributions in knowing what would help the global economy obama has reported that immelt has emerged as one of his top economic advisors in regards to trying to rebuild americas economy on january   president obama announced immelts appointment as chairman of his outside panel of economic advisers succeeding former federal reserve chairman paul volcker the new york times reported that obamas appointment of immelt was another strong signal that he intends to make the white house more businessfriendly the council met a total of four times with its final meeting on january   in  the authorization for the council was not renewed causing the council to be permanently shut down honorsedit jeff immelt has earned significant honors throughout his career beginning with his graduation from dartmouth cum laude and earning the earl hamilton varsity award as a college football player for friendship and character later in  he received the robert fletcher award from dartmouths thayer school of engineering career honorsedit barrons has named immelt one of the worlds best ceos three times he is a member of the american academy of arts  sciences the financial times named him man of the year in  immelt was named to time magazines  most influential people in the world in  immelt was awarded the  american football coaches association tuss mclaughry award given to a distinguished american or americans for the highest distinction in service to others in accepting the award he said i am a product of football and i owe a great debt of gratitude to that system what i learned playing football enters my life every day  in april  immelt won the th edition of the leonardo international prize as a foreigner who reinforced his countrys cultural and economic ties with italy  on  december  immelt was listed by ukbased company richtopia at number  in the list of  most influential ceos commencement addressesedit he has been awarded approximately ten honorary doctorates and has given more than this number of university speeches including commencement addresses after becoming chairman of ge immelt delivered his first university address to the  graduating class of the thayer school of engineering at dartmouth college of which he is an alumnus as their investiture speaker he gave the college commencement address and received an honorary doctor of laws from dartmouth in june  on february   shortly after becoming ges chairman and ceo immelt gave a town hall speech at georgia institute of technology as a guest of their president in the years that followed immelt gave the commencement address at northeastern university  and received the honorary doctorate of business administration he returned to georgia tech in the spring of  as their commencement speaker he was commencement speaker at the university of notre dame on may   where he was awarded the honorary doctor of laws he was commencement speaker at the worcester polytechnic institute on may   and received an honorary degree immelt served as commencement speaker at michigan state universitys  pm ceremony on december   and was awarded an honorary doctorate of business he was the commencement speaker on may   at hamilton college which awarded him its honorary doctor of laws and on may   at boston college where he was awarded the honorary doctor of business administration he addressed the undergraduate class of  of the university of maryland baltimore county on may   and received an honorary doctor of public service  degree despite controversy at the school over ges corporate tax strategies in may  he delivered the commencement address at the university of connecticut graduate school and was awarded an honorary doctor of humane letters in  he delivered the commencement address at siena college where he was also awarded the honorary doctor of humanities in  immelt spoke at the commencement for clemson universitys college of arts architecture and humanities as well as the college of engineering and science clemson awarded immelt with an honorary doctorate and immelt spoke of how ge hired many clemson alumni at their gas turbine factory in greenville south carolina personal lifeedit immelt is married to his wife andrea and they have one daughter sarah they live in connecticut their purchase of an apartment in new york was featured in a forbes article referencesedit  smyth sean  general electric ceo jeff immelt is stepping down the boston globe retrieved    immelt jeffrey r – encyclopediacom retrieved    byrum keller valerie  immel and imel families in america twigs and bran