 and will remain chairman of the board of directors of ge for a transition period through december   prior to holding this position immelt served as ge’s president and chairmanelect from november  until september  and as a senior vice president of ge and president and ceo ge medical systems from  until november  immelt began his career at ge in  in corporate marketing and held various leadership positions in ge’s plastics appliances and healthcare businesses immelt currently serves as a member of president trump’s committee on american manufacturing and previously served as the chair of president obama’s council on jobs and competitiveness and as a director of the federal reserve bank of new york home investors newsroom lets stay in touch   general electric jeff immelt ceo  gecom we are transforming ge into the worlds premierdigital industrial companyusing our scale anddiversity todrive outcomesfor customers a company that understands where it fits in the markets and in society and appreciates its responsibility to both the ninth chairman of ge a post he has held since september   jeffrey r immelt chairman and ceo print profile download headshot download images mr immelt has held several global leadership positions since coming to ge in  including roles in ges plastics appliances and healthcare businesses in  he became an officer of ge and joined the ge capital board in  mr immelt has been named one of the worlds best ceos three times by barrons and since he began serving as chief executive officer ge has been named americas most admired company in a poll conducted by fortune magazine and one of the worlds most respected companies in polls by barrons and the financial times mr immelt was the chair of president obamas council on jobs and competitiveness he is a member of the american academy of arts  sciences mr immelt earned a ba degree in applied mathematics from dartmouth college in  and an mba from harvard university in  he and his wife have one daughter     ente