melt had headed up ges medical systems division now known as ge healthcare as its president and ceo effective august   immelt will step down as ges ceo contents  early life  career  general electric  background  crisis management  strategy  divestitures  acquisitions and investments  performance  employment  controversies  compensation and retirement  philanthropy  charitable activities  public service  honors  career honors  commencement addresses  personal life  references  further reading  external links early lifeedit immelt was born in cincinnati the son of donna rosemary née wallace a school teacher and joseph francis immelt who managed the general electric aircraft engines division geae is now known as ge aviation immelt attended finneytown high school he played football in college and was an offensive tackle he earned an ab in applied mathematics and economics cum laude  from dartmouth college graduating with the class of  he was president of his fraternity phi delta alpha and currently serves on the dartmouth board of trustees during his years at dartmouth he worked summers on a ford assembly line in cincinnati after graduating he worked for procter and gamble before matriculating at harvard for his mba immelt earned his mba from harvard business school graduating in  he described business school as one of the most intense times of your life  careeredit general electricedit backgroundedit immelt has been with ge since  when he graduated from harvard with his mba he held a number of increasingly senior positions in ges plastics appliances and healthcare businesses he became a ge officer in  joined the ge capital board in  and took on the leadership of ge healthcare before being named ceo the competition for the ceo position that immelt won began when jack welch asked gary wendt the head of ge financial services inc then a  billion empire and ges most profitable division to resign on the theory that he would overshadow welchs other candidates immelt surpassed robert nardelli who was so close to welch that his nickname was little jack and james mcnerney nardelli would leave ge to head home depot and then chrysler and mcnerney left ge to lead m before going on to lead boeing immelt was selected by the ge board in november  to succeed welch as ceo of ge he served as ges president and chairmanelect for ten months before taking the position of chairman and ceo of ge on september   he will retire from ge on december   crisis managementedit immelt has been thrust into three significant external crises since taking the lead at ge as chairman on september   almost immediately he faced the  terrorist attacks he then was pressed to defend ges business model and the quality of its financial reports as the economy reeled from the enron crisis in  he shepherded ge through the united states financial crisis his tenure as chairman and ceo started off on a low note – he took over the role on september   just four days before the terrorist attacks on the united states which killed two employees and cost ges insurance business  million as well as having a direct effect on the companys aircraft engines sector immelt defended ges reporting elections and the quality of its financial statements following heightened scrutiny after the enron crisis in  his first year end as ceo immelt famously offered the market and the sec a choice in financial reports a new dramatically expanded set of reports with more details versus what had been the traditional format for ges sec filings the experiment seemed to confirm that the traditional format which was shorter was preferable and it continues to be used at ge today immelts intuition and judgments about financial reporting transparency were validated in experiments in behavioral economics conducted at princeton in  immelt has led ge through two reporting challenges since then it has been required to restate its sec filings and in  ge agreed to pay the sec  million to settle allegations of accounting fraud ge could not escape the  crisis that was fueled by the mortgagebacked securities debacle on wall street and the liquidity crisis that brought the derivatives market to its knees ges major financial business is known as ge capital and it is operated largely through the general electric credit corporation subsidiary as part of its response to the credit crisis ge joined goldman sachs and morgan stanley in forming a wholly owned banking affiliate that qualified as a savings and loan association this entitles the subsidiary to fdic insurance over its deposit at the cost of bowing to regulation as a bank holding company aid received from the federal reserve by ge has also become a political issue in the  presidential campaign strategyedit immelt has not been a passive inheritor of the house that jack built  in fact at the outset of this time as ges ceo immelt took pains to establish that he would act as his own man  welch preferred internal or organic growth and benefited from longterm us economic trends that buoyed his major business lines in particular welchs tenure benefited from the economic expansion during the clinton administration which ended immediately before immelt became ges ceo the us economy has faced a number of shocks since immelt became ceo the  terrorist attacks on the usa the  financial crisis and the recessionary quarters under the obama administration immelts governance has taken a different path differentiating him from welch in both substance and style on the one hand he has eliminated or reduced ges involvement in a number of businesses from the welch era with moves in the plastics appliance and ge capital businesses on the other hand he has seized the growing international nature of commerce to expand ges operations overseas divestituresedit the ge plastics business was sold in  for  billion to saudi arabian interests welch had been the leader of ges plastics business before being named its overall ceo in  ge agreed to sell its appliance business for  billion  in  immelt completed the sale of nbc universal to comcast for  billion in april  ge announced a major series of reorganization steps it plans to sell its real estate business for  billion sell most of its ge capital assets which now total  billion and repatriate nearly  billion in cash held overseas to fund while the board also authorized a share buyback program using up to  billion this plan confirms ges intent to exit the banking business acquisitions and investmentsedit immelts reorganization of ge has been accomplished in part through a number of acquisitions he underscored the riskiness of an acquisitionbased growth strategy in  when he said you cant do a lot of deals and have them all be great  geographically his strategy has focused on two areas china and europe ges efforts in china have been central to immelts vision in july  immelts general electric announced that it is in the process of relocating its xray division from wisconsin to china immelt had previously referred to china as ges second home market immelt initiated one of his first major acquisitions in his area of operating expertise the medical business in  ge bought uk based amerhsam plc for  billion ge is currently attempting to complete its acquisition of alstom france businesses for an enterprise value of  billion  at the same time immelt has taken a number of actions that have been controversial with some leading to bad publicity a major headline grabber has been the reduction in ges workforce at the same time that immelt served on a presidential council whose aim was to increase us employment see public service section performanceedit on march   according to its fiscal  sec form k ge had  shares of voting common stock outstanding with an aggregate market value  billion on march   on january   according to its fiscal  sec form k ge had  shares of voting common stock outstanding with an aggregate market value of at least  billion on the last business day of ges most recently completed second fiscal quarter since taking over ges stock price has dropped  while income has risen from  billion in  to  billion in  at the ten year mark of immelts tenure at ge its stock price had dropped  from its levels when he took over during that same year period ge has paid out  billion in dividends the sp  index has roughly doubled in value since immelt took over employmentedit at the end of  when immelt replaced welch ge employed  worldwide and  in the us as reported in its sec form k for  ges sec form k for  states that worldwide employment is  and us employment is  these employment levels have varied significantly under immelt general electric year end employment has varied from  in  to  in  a net increase of  employment had dropped from  in  to  in  controversiesedit immelt has been associated in the press with a number of public controversies he is working with the nfl to find a constructive medical solution to the headtrauma injury issues faced by football players of all types immelts role concerning employment and unemployment is his greatest controversy he served on a presidential council whose goal included increasing employment in the us while leading ge during more than a decade of volatility in the number of people it employs those believing his business roles contributed to unemployment have demonstrated at his college speeches the number of people employed by ge has been volatile as a performance statistic both rising and falling that volatility reflects both ge cost cutting efforts under ge and the acquisition and sale of several large businesses each with their own significant number of employees immelts strategies have contributed to a buildup of cash at the end of  over  billion had been kept offshore to avoid a special federal repatriation tax as such ge is a member of a controversial group of american companies experiencing trapped cash thought to exceed  trillion across this group of corporations in  ge announced a repatriation program for part of its cash balances after the us fiscal crisis of – immelt reduced ges dividends to conserve capital and internal funding causing a negative reaction among some dividendoriented investors he recently began a public campaign to press the state of connecticut for local tax benefits and threatened to move some of ges operations out of the state if the benefits were not forthcoming as chairman and ceo of ge immelt has come under attack for leading ge towards legally avoiding paying us federal corporate taxes ges tax positions have become a major item in immelts agenda ges local taxes in connecticut have increased  times since  and the state had approved yet another revised tax policy in early  immelt threatened to move ges headquarters out of connecticut if the state would not back away from the tax plan during the us presidential elections in  ge came under attack for not paying us federal taxes while receiving substantial federal tax benefits while the tax attacks created the impression that ge paid no taxes its worldwide tax expense was over  billion with most of the taxes paid in foreign jurisdictions ge is reported to have paid no federal us taxes in  compensation and retirementedit immelts compensation has fluctuated significantly as ceo of general electric in  immelt earned a total compensation of  in  he earned a total compensation of  in  immelt earned a total compensation of  in  immelts compensation nearly doubled to  million immelt had a total five year compensation of  million through  an income which ranked sixth among executives employed by usbased conglomerates some components of his total compensation package over the years have been newsworthy in some years he was granted stock options at  and in other years he was paid no bonusin  his compensation totalled  million a decrease from his  compensation of  million that  compensation had risen  over his  compensation of  million on june   ge announced that is chairman and ceo jeffrey r immelt wou